OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGlasgow education chief:   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FSchools were excluding     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fpupils out of habit        
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, When Maureen McKenna was six weeks into
OL,6, her job as Glasgow's director of       
OL,7, education, staff at one of her schools 
OL,8, were threatening to go out on strike.  
OL,10,FA pupil at Drumchapel High had brought 
OL,11,Fa weapon in to class and she was       
OL,12,Frefusing a request for him to be       
OL,13,Fpermanently excluded.                  
OL,15,F"I got a phone call from the union rep 
OL,16,Fand he said staff were voting to go out
OL,17,Fon strike," she says.                  
OL,19,FMs McKenna says she "took a deep       
OL,20,Fbreath" and told him the staff must do 
OL,21,Fwhat they had to do.                   
